public int compareTo(java.lang.Object o)
Compares this move to another move. The implementation is strictly defective - it ought to do something other than throw a ClassCastException if o is not a Move, but for optimization reasons it doesn't. This class is only partially ordered. That is, the ordering is incompatible with equals.
